# Coral Protocol Hackathon Submission: IORA MCP Adapter

## Overview

IORA (Intelligent Oracle Rust Assistant) is a multi-source cryptocurrency data aggregator with AI-powered market analysis and Solana oracle integration. This submission provides a production-grade MCP (Multi-Agent Communication Protocol) adapter that enables Coral Studio to interact with IORA's core functionality.

## Features Delivered

‚úÖ **Production MCP Adapter** - Zero-trust HTTP API with HMAC authentication
‚úÖ **Multi-Provider LLM Support** - Gemini, Mistral, AI-ML API with provider selection
‚úÖ **Real Data Integration** - No mocks; shells out to actual IORA binary
‚úÖ **Structured JSON Contracts** - Deterministic I/O schemas for all tools
‚úÖ **Security Hardened** - Rate limiting, request validation, error sanitization, kill-switch
‚úÖ **Observability** - Structured logging with request tracing (redacted)
‚úÖ **NFT Receipt Minting** - Crossmint custodial receipts for oracle transactions
‚úÖ **E2E Tests** - Real integration tests hitting devnet
‚úÖ **Docker Ready** - One-command deployment via docker-compose
‚úÖ **Judge-Proof Demo** - Makefile, demo.sh, OpenAPI, Postman collection

## 90-Second Judge Demo Script

### Prerequisites Setup (2 minutes)

```bash
# 1. Clone, build, and run
git clone <repo-url> iora && cd iora
make build
export CORAL_SHARED_SECRET=<random-hex>
export GEMINI_API_KEY=... # or MISTRAL_API_KEY / AIMLAPI_API_KEY
make run &
sleep 3

# 2. Smoke test (optional)
make demo
```

### Demo Flow (90 seconds)

```bash
